div.div:
The first stage of StocKings execution is obtaining details of Large Cap companies in user-defined countries (As default we go for: Germany, France, UK and US)
Company Names, Tickers and Market Cap are scraped from:
https://companiesmarketcap.com/
The details are saved in LargeCaps.xlsx - the file which is the basis for further processing

div.div:
Tickers which are stored in LargeCaps.xlsx are processed ticker by ticker.
YahooFinanceParser extracts historical prices and dividends details by scraping from Yahoo Finance. It calculates simple measures of price changes.
The final output of script is LargeCapsPrices.xlsx.
